01:08:13.040 --> 01:08:15.780
&gt;&gt; What was your observation
of the economic developments

01:08:15.780 --> 01:08:18.840
of North Korea based
on what you're seeing,

01:08:18.840 --> 01:08:23.210
is it [inaudible] progressing
on economic development here

01:08:23.210 --> 01:08:27.020
in manufacturing or
agriculture or both?

01:08:27.020 --> 01:08:29.290
&gt;&gt; Curtis Melvin: Yeah, you
know, it's a big mystery.

01:08:29.290 --> 01:08:33.260
I mean, you know, North
Korea has never --

01:08:33.260 --> 01:08:37.440 position:56%
they stopped publishing net material
product tables in the 1960's.

01:08:37.440 --> 01:08:40.460
Net material product
tables were what we used

01:08:40.460 --> 01:08:44.370
from other communist countries to
estimate the size of their GDP.

01:08:44.370 --> 01:08:46.750
There is an entire
literature on this

01:08:46.750 --> 01:08:51.020 position:56%
and I'll spare you the
complications, but it's a lot of art

01:08:51.020 --> 01:08:54.970
and science, it's a rigorous
attempt but it's not perfect

01:08:54.970 --> 01:08:57.570
to establish a value for
official output in North Korea.

01:08:57.570 --> 01:09:06.380
But now there's a black market in
North Korea and there's not even --

01:09:06.380 --> 01:09:13.670
the government hasn't published a
budget since 2001 and, you know,

01:09:13.670 --> 01:09:17.290
they only publish percent
increases and decreases in spending

01:09:17.290 --> 01:09:18.810
on selected items each year.

01:09:18.810 --> 01:09:22.130
It's mostly an advertising
or signaling device,

01:09:22.130 --> 01:09:24.120
it's not anything you can use

01:09:24.120 --> 01:09:29.330
to rigorously estimate
the official budget.

01:09:29.330 --> 01:09:36.900
So really the big good news I guess
economically from North Korea is

01:09:36.900 --> 01:09:41.780
that they've stopped
the inflation that began

01:09:41.780 --> 01:09:46.220 position:56%
after the 2009 currency revaluation.

01:09:46.220 --> 01:09:49.410
We don't really know how
they've stopped this inflation,

01:09:49.410 --> 01:09:52.640
but the black market exchange
rate has been relatively stable

01:09:52.640 --> 01:09:57.820
for the one since 2012.

01:09:57.820 --> 01:10:02.650
The number of markets that exist

01:10:02.650 --> 01:10:06.310
in the country have increased
a little bit under Kim Jong-Il,

01:10:06.310 --> 01:10:10.290
but he's shown no propensity
like his father to clampdown

01:10:10.290 --> 01:10:15.870
on market activity or
to restrict free prices

01:10:15.870 --> 01:10:19.760
of commodities in those markets.

01:10:19.760 --> 01:10:22.120
And he still hasn't visited one,

01:10:22.120 --> 01:10:26.340
we still haven't seen any official
North Korean person involved

01:10:26.340 --> 01:10:32.220
in economic matters visit
an official marketplace.

01:10:32.220 --> 01:10:36.030
But we can see on satellite imagery
that they're continuing to grow

01:10:36.030 --> 01:10:43.500
and expand, so that's
a positive development.

01:10:43.500 --> 01:10:48.130
The South Korean Bank of Korea
publishes an annual estimate

01:10:48.130 --> 01:10:53.070
of the North Korean economy and
they've shown basically a plus

01:10:53.070 --> 01:10:57.940
or minus 1% each year since
Kim Jong-Il took office.

01:10:57.940 --> 01:11:05.640
A lot of people, myself included,
think that the actual growth rate,

01:11:05.640 --> 01:11:08.080
at least in Pyongyang has
been substantially higher

01:11:08.080 --> 01:11:12.540
than that just based on qualitative
assessments on the amounts

01:11:12.540 --> 01:11:14.930 position:56%
of consumer goods that are available

01:11:14.930 --> 01:11:18.820
to North Koreans today
compared to say 10 years ago.

01:11:20.660 --> 01:11:28.190
You cannot defend that position
with any standard econometric tools

01:11:28.190 --> 01:11:32.740
because the data is not
available to do that.

01:11:32.740 --> 01:11:37.590
We're really trying to
triangulate official economic news,

01:11:37.590 --> 01:11:42.000
satellite information,
information from defectors,

01:11:42.000 --> 01:11:44.540
information that creeps
across the border

01:11:44.540 --> 01:11:47.060
to put together a coherent
picture of what's happening

01:11:47.060 --> 01:11:54.900
in specific industries and
that's really the best we can do.

